    "Ubbens and Stavness (2018) 38.",
    "PlantVillage 13,262 Tomato crop disease classification was done using photos from the PlantVillage dataset and pre-trained deep learning architecture, specifically AlexNet and VGG16 net.",
    "The classification accuracy for VGG16 net was 97.29%, while for AlexNet, it was 97.49%.",
    "Rangarajan et al. (2018) 39.",
    "Cornell University data set 18,222 The biggest publicly accessible image set annotated for specific plant disease, the three data sets collectively comprise 18,222 photos tagged with 105,705 NLB lesions."
